.TH "__snd_hda_add_vmaster" 9 "__snd_hda_add_vmaster" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__snd_hda_add_vmaster \- create a virtual master control and add followers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __snd_hda_add_vmaster
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "char *name "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *tlv "  ","
.BI "const char * const *followers "  ","
.BI "const char *suffix "  ","
.BI "bool init_follower_vol "  ","
.BI "struct snd_kcontrol **ctl_ret "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
HD-audio codec
.IP "name" 12
vmaster control name
.IP "tlv" 12
TLV data (optional)
.IP "followers" 12
follower control names (optional)
.IP "suffix" 12
suffix string to each follower name (optional)
.IP "init_follower_vol" 12
initialize followers to unmute/0dB
.IP "ctl_ret" 12
store the vmaster kcontrol in return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a virtual master control with the given name.  The TLV data
must be either NULL or a valid data.

\fIfollowers\fP is a NULL-terminated array of strings, each of which is a
follower control name.  All controls with these names are assigned to
the new virtual master control.

This function returns zero if successful or a negative error code.
